##This is Wuhan"pestilence"the line most true rescue actual situation | a foot steps into the gate of death, be dragged back by US ABRUPTLY!

Sh-scalpel

Functional introduction, Shanghai Medical Surgical cattle gathering place, your side of the surgical experts.

Expert Clinic | rational drug use | focus | surgery day | medical history

Surgery Day
The Thrill of the O.R

Press
It's dangerous, it happens all the time...

1

Only from the isolation ward out, 24 hours, 10 people team intubation 20 times, fast exhausted ~ ~ ~ ~ fortunately basically met some critically ill patients mechanical ventilation needs.

It's dangerous. It happens all the time.

After thinking about it for a long time, I would like to put this video up. It doesn't matter if you can't understand the instrument, just read the word.

Not Modest, this is the Wuhan epidemic the most true first-line rescue live, is I in the isolation ward with the contaminated area dedicated mobile phone shot.

In this patient, Oxygenation was only 60% , consciousness was lost, blood pressure collapsed undetectable, and heart rate presented with a sinister tachycardia.

Anesthesiologists quickly give medicine / Mask Oxygen / intubation... In the course of rescue, the patient's heart rate once "a word stop plate" , immediately do cardiopulmonary resuscitation, give epinephrine, do electrical defibrillation.

Fortunately, the patient's condition stabilized rapidly, and his heart rate came back, from 60 to 70 to 83,84,87... Oxygenation slowly back up.

It's one foot in the grave, and we're dragging it right back. It feels good to save a life!

The anesthesiologist who performed the rescue was nearly on the floor when the nurse teacher at the second hospital in Zhongshan, Guangzhou, radioed the office that the patient was getting better

PS, every time we appear, must be in critical condition. Normal people are at least 95% Oxygenation, but we are exposed to patients with low Oxygenation, less than 80% of Oxygenation, will not last a few hours, we are competing with death.

2

My name is Ling, and I'm an anesthesiologist at Wuhan Union Hospital. After the video, let's talk about our critical life support team.

Early, because of the particularity of anesthesiology work, I only a few times to the fever clinic / Isolation Ward support, to tell the truth, really can not afford the "outbreak line" called.

On the 13th of this month, I, together with more than 10 key members of the Department of anesthesiology, formed the emergency intubation commando team, or "intubation team" , which rushed to the isolation ward of the West Hospital and really went to the fire line.

As we set off, we smiled and said, "intubation" does not seem to be a strong enough statement, should be called "kamikaze team.

Why? In a word, the airway opens directly -- as if it were at the highest risk of inhalation exposure!

Many patients with severe pneumonia require suction therapy. For this treatment, a tube is placed through the mouth into the trachea and is connected to the suction tube, allowing the inhalation to proceed. An anesthesiologist is usually required to perform the task of inserting the catheter into the trachea. Most hospitals now use a classic Laryngoscope, in which the anesthesiologist's eye must be close to the patient's mouth to see the opening, so that the tube can be inserted properly. The minute the catheter goes in, the patient's Airways Gush With super-strong Aerosol!

I think it goes without saying how dangerous this process is?

Share our anesthesiologist Emergency Airway intubation precautions: isolation + protective clothing, N95 mask + surgical mask, goggles + splash screen, two layer surgical gloves, surgical caps, double layer shoe covers. Only this level of protection (level 2.5, less than level 3 without a positive pressure hood) will be effective in protecting the doctor.

Even if the protection is in place, every day in contact with confirmed cases, a lot of cough, the total unexpected. As we all know, N95 only blocks 95% of the pests, daily exposure, if the resistance is low, the virus load is strong vitality, will be infected.

WHO's not afraid of infection? When you're in the field, you don't have to worry about it. Hopefully, with the LARYNGOSCOPE and Catheter in hand, we'll be able to take more lives from COVID19.

This city, the people of this city, have suffered too much. May It all be over soon.
